  "prompt": "What should you engrave on promise rings?",
  "response": "Engraving on promise rings is a personal choice and should reflect the meaning and sentiment behind the ring. Here are some meaningful ideas for what to engrave:\n\n### Names or Initials\n- Your names (e.g., \"Alex & Taylor\")\n- Your initials (e.g., \"A + T\" or \"A&T\")\n\n### Dates\n- The date you met or started your relationship (e.g., \"03.14.2020\")\n- A meaningful date in your relationship\n\n### Short Phrases or Words\n- \"Forever Yours\"\n- \"Always & Forever\"\n- \"My Promise\"\n- \"One Love\"\n- \"Soulmates\"\n- \"Eternal\"\n- \"Endless Love\"\n- \"My Heart\"\n\n### Quotes or Song Lyrics\n- A meaningful line from a song or poem (e.g., \"All of me loves all of you\")\n- A short, romantic quote (e.g., \"You are my today and all of my tomorrows\")\n\n### Symbols\n- Infinity symbol (\u221e) to represent eternal love\n- A heart symbol (\u2764\ufe0f)\n- Coordinates of a special place\n\n### Inside Jokes or Nicknames\n- A nickname only the two of you use\n- A playful or meaningful inside joke\n\n### Promises\n- \"I Choose You\"\n- \"Together Always\"\n- \"Promise to Be True\"\n\nWhen choosing an engraving, keep it concise and meaningful. The engraving size is usually limited, so shorter phrases or symbols work best. Discuss it with your partner to ensure it\u2019s something that resonates with both of you.",
